# Blog Routes Accessibility Audit
**Date**: 2025-10-21
**Target**: Blog route pages (app/blog/*.tsx)
**WCAG Level**: 2.1 AA

## Blog Index Page (app/blog/page.tsx)

### Document Structure
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Page uses semantic HTML landmarks
- `<header>` element for page header
- `<article>` elements for each blog post
- Implicit `<main>` landmark from Next.js App Router layout

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 1.3.1 Info and Relationships (Level A)
- 2.4.1 Bypass Blocks (Level A)

### Heading Hierarchy
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Page title: `<h1>` "Blog"
- Tag section: `<h2>` "Browse by topic"
- Each post title: `<h2>` (within article context)
- No skipped heading levels

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 1.3.1 Info and Relationships (Level A)
- 2.4.6 Headings and Labels (Level AA)

### Navigation (Tag Cloud)
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Tags use Next.js Link component (client-side navigation)
- Each tag displays post count (e.g., "Next.js (5)")
- Links have descriptive text (tag name + count)
- Visual distinction: Background color + hover state
- Keyboard accessible (native link behavior)

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 2.4.4 Link Purpose (In Context) (Level A)
- 2.1.1 Keyboard (Level A)

### Post Listings
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Each post wrapped in `<article>` element
- Post title: `<h2>` with link to full post
- Metadata uses semantic `<time>` element with dateTime attribute
- Separation indicators (•) are decorative text (no ARIA needed)
- Tags displayed as visual badges (not interactive in list view)
- Empty state message for no posts

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 1.3.1 Info and Relationships (Level A)
- 3.2.4 Consistent Identification (Level AA)

### Time Elements
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Proper `<time>` element with `dateTime` attribute
- Machine-readable ISO format in dateTime
- Human-readable format displayed
- Consistent date formatting across posts

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 1.3.1 Info and Relationships (Level A)

### Responsive Design
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Max-width container (max-w-4xl) for readability
- Horizontal padding (px-4) prevents edge clipping
- Flex-wrap on metadata prevents overflow
- Tag cloud wraps on narrow screens

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 1.4.10 Reflow (Level AA)

## Blog Post Page (app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx)

### Document Structure
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- `<article>` element wraps entire post
- `<header>` element for post metadata
- Implicit `<main>` landmark from layout
- Post content in semantic div with prose classes

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 1.3.1 Info and Relationships (Level A)
- 2.4.1 Bypass Blocks (Level A)

### Heading Hierarchy
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Post title: `<h1>` (single h1 per page)
- MDX content headings: h2-h6 (rendered via mdxComponents)
- No skipped levels in structure

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 2.4.6 Headings and Labels (Level AA)

### Metadata Section
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- `<time>` element with dateTime attribute
- Author name displayed as text
- Reading time displayed (optional field)
- Metadata separators (•) are decorative
- Consistent formatting with index page

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 1.3.1 Info and Relationships (Level A)
- 3.2.4 Consistent Identification (Level AA)

### Tag Links
**Status**: ⚠️ WARNING - Inconsistent element usage
- Tags use `<a href>` instead of Next.js Link component
- Other pages (index, tag archive) use Link component
- Links are functional but inconsistent with architecture
- Href generation: `/blog/tag/${tag.toLowerCase().replace(/\s+/g, '-')}`

**Recommendation**: Replace `<a href>` with `<Link href>` for consistency
**Impact**: Low (still keyboard accessible, just missing client-side routing optimization)

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 2.1.1 Keyboard (Level A) - Still accessible
- 3.2.4 Consistent Identification (Level AA) - Minor inconsistency

### Featured Image
**Status**: ⚠️ WARNING - Missing alt attribute enforcement
- Featured image uses standard `<img>` tag (not Next.js Image)
- Alt text set to `frontmatter.title` (not ideal - should be image description)
- Missing width/height attributes (may cause layout shift)
- No Next.js Image optimization

**Recommendations**:
1. Use Next.js Image component for optimization
2. Add dedicated `featuredImageAlt` field to frontmatter
3. Fallback to title only if alt text not provided

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 1.1.1 Non-text Content (Level A) - Alt present but not descriptive

### MDX Content Rendering
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- MDXRemote component renders content
- Components from mdxComponents.tsx applied
- rehype-highlight for syntax highlighting
- remark-gfm for GitHub Flavored Markdown
- Prose classes for typography

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- Dependent on mdxComponents.tsx audit (see a11y-components.log)

### SEO Metadata (generateMetadata)
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Metadata generated from frontmatter
- OpenGraph tags for social sharing
- Twitter card metadata
- Published time for articles
- Author attribution

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 2.4.2 Page Titled (Level A)

## Tag Archive Page (app/blog/tag/[tag]/page.tsx)

### Document Structure
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Same structure as blog index page
- `<header>` element for page header
- `<article>` elements for posts
- Implicit `<main>` landmark

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 1.3.1 Info and Relationships (Level A)
- 2.4.1 Bypass Blocks (Level A)

### Heading Hierarchy
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Page title: `<h1>` with tagged term highlighted
- Each post: `<h2>` (consistent with index)
- No skipped levels

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 2.4.6 Headings and Labels (Level AA)

### Navigation
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- "Back to all posts" link at top
- Clear link text with arrow indicator (←)
- Uses Next.js Link component
- Keyboard accessible

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 2.4.4 Link Purpose (In Context) (Level A)
- 3.2.3 Consistent Navigation (Level AA)

### Current Tag Indication
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Current tag highlighted with blue background + white text
- Other tags: gray background
- Visual distinction does not rely solely on color (also different background intensity)
- Screen readers will read all tags equally (no special ARIA needed)

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 1.4.1 Use of Color (Level A)
- 1.4.3 Contrast (Minimum) (Level AA)

### Post Count Display
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Results count in page description
- Format: "X post(s) found"
- Pluralization handled correctly
- Clear user feedback

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 3.3.1 Error Identification (Level A) - Not error, but feedback
- 3.3.2 Labels or Instructions (Level A)

### Empty State (404)
**Status**: ✅ PASSED
- Returns 404 via notFound() if no posts for tag
- Proper HTTP status code
- Next.js handles 404 page rendering

**WCAG Criteria Met**:
- 3.3.1 Error Identification (Level A)

## Summary

### Blog Index (app/blog/page.tsx)
**Status**: ✅ PASSED (WCAG 2.1 AA Compliant)
- Violations: 0
- Warnings: 0

### Blog Post Page (app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx)
**Status**: ⚠️ PASSED WITH WARNINGS
- Violations: 0
- Warnings: 2
  1. Tag links use `<a>` instead of `<Link>` (inconsistent)
  2. Featured image lacks descriptive alt text + optimization

### Tag Archive Page (app/blog/tag/[tag]/page.tsx)
**Status**: ✅ PASSED (WCAG 2.1 AA Compliant)
- Violations: 0
- Warnings: 0

### Overall Routes Assessment
**Status**: ✅ PASSED (WCAG 2.1 AA Compliant)

All blog routes use proper semantic HTML with landmark regions. Minor improvements recommended for tag links and featured image handling, but no WCAG violations present.
